1. DEFINITIONS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

"Software" means the source code, compiled code, documentation, and any
other files made available under this License.

"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the
Software in whole or in part, including forks, ports, adaptations,
translations, or modifications, whether or not distributed as a separate
package.

"You" (or "Your") means the individual or legal entity exercising the
rights granted by this License. For legal entities, "You" includes all
entities that control, are controlled by, or are under common control
with the contracting entity, where "control" means ownership of more
than fifty percent (50%) of the voting shares or equivalent.

"Annual Gross Revenue" means the total gross revenue or gross income of
You from all sources and all activities, for a given calendar year,
expressed in United States Dollars (USD). Revenue earned in other
currencies shall be converted to USD at the average mid-market exchange
rate for that calendar year as published by the European Central Bank.
Annual Gross Revenue is determined at the entity level as defined above,
not at the level of a single product or project.

"Licensor" means Jan Mašarski, the copyright holder of the Software.

"License Month" means each calendar month during which You use,
distribute, or otherwise exercise any rights under this License.


