3. USAGE FEE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

3.1  Free Use

  Use of the Software is free of charge if Your Annual Gross Revenue
  for the most recently completed calendar year is less than
  USD 100,000.

  If You are a new entity with no completed calendar year of revenue,
  the free threshold applies until the end of Your first full calendar
  year of operation.

3.2  Fee Schedule

  If Your Annual Gross Revenue for the most recently completed calendar
  year meets or exceeds the thresholds below, You are required to pay
  the Licensor a monthly fee for each License Month:

  ┌────────────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────┐
  │ Annual Gross Revenue (USD)             │ Monthly Fee (USD) │
  ├────────────────────────────────────────┼───────────────────┤
  │ 100,000 – 999,999                      │              10   │
  │ 1,000,000 – 9,999,999                  │             100   │
  │ 10,000,000 and above                   │           1,000   │
  └────────────────────────────────────────┴───────────────────┘

  The applicable fee tier is reassessed each January 1 based on the
  Annual Gross Revenue of the preceding calendar year. If Your revenue
  crosses a threshold during the year, the new tier applies from
  January 1 of the following year; mid-year adjustments are not
  required.

3.3  Payment Timing

  The monthly fee for each License Month is due no later than the
  15th day of the immediately following calendar month (e.g., the
  fee for March is due by April 15).

  For Your first License Month, the fee is due within thirty (30) days
  of the date on which You first exercise any rights under this License.

  The simplest and recommended method of compliance is to set up a
  recurring monthly sponsorship at the applicable amount, which
  satisfies this obligation automatically.

3.4  Payment Method

  Fees must be paid via GitHub Sponsors at:

    https://github.com/sponsors/yanmasharski

  The Licensor may designate additional or alternative payment methods
  by publishing notice in the repository containing this License.

3.5  Self-Reporting and Good Faith

  You are solely responsible for accurately determining Your Annual
  Gross Revenue and paying the applicable fee. This License operates
  on the basis of good faith self-reporting. No invoice will be issued
  by the Licensor. Knowingly misrepresenting Your Annual Gross Revenue
  to reduce or avoid a fee obligation constitutes a material breach of
  this License and may constitute fraud under applicable law.

3.6  Grace Period

  If You fail to pay a fee by the applicable due date under Section 3.3,
  You have thirty (30) days from that due date (the "Grace Period") to
  cure the breach by paying all outstanding fees. If full payment is
  not received within the Grace Period, this License terminates
  automatically pursuant to Section 8.


