8.1  Automatic Termination

  This License and all rights granted hereunder terminate automatically,
  without notice from the Licensor, if You:

  (a) fail to pay any applicable fee within the Grace Period specified
      in Section 3.6; or

  (b) materially breach any other obligation under this License and
      fail to cure such breach within thirty (30) days of becoming
      aware of it.

8.2  Effect of Termination

  Upon termination of this License:

  (a) all rights granted to You immediately and irrevocably cease;

  (b) any continued use, reproduction, modification, or distribution
      of the Software or Derivative Works constitutes copyright
      infringement and may give rise to civil and criminal liability
      under applicable law;

  (c) You must immediately cease all exercise of rights under this
      License and destroy or remove all copies of the Software and
      Derivative Works in Your possession or control.

8.3  Reinstatement

  The Licensor may, at their sole and absolute discretion, reinstate
  this License upon written confirmation that all outstanding fees have
  been paid and all breaches have been cured. Reinstatement, if granted,
  is prospective only and does not waive or release any claims arising
  from the period of termination. No reinstatement is guaranteed.

8.4  Survival

  The following sections survive any termination or expiration of this
  License: Section 1 (Definitions), Section 5 (Attribution, with
  respect to any distributions made prior to termination), Section 6
  (Disclaimer of Warranties), Section 7 (Limitation of Liability),
  Section 8.2 (Effect of Termination), Section 9 (Intellectual
  Property), and Section 10 (General Provisions).


